<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1526,1841]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,420,1526,1552]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Nomenclatural notes:—</emphasis>
<materialsCitation collectionCode="B, A" collectorName="Horto Berolinensis. Berg &amp; Villavicencio" country="Cuba" location="Cuba" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" specimenCode="B100516451" specimenCount="3" typeStatus="holotype">
In the protologue it is not mentioned in which herbarium the type was deposited, but only that the type comes from 
<collectingCountry box="[375,434,1562,1588]" name="Cuba" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(seeds), sent by Otto, to 
<collectorName box="[717,998,1562,1589]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Horto Berolinensis. Berg</collectorName>
&amp; 
<collectorName box="[1034,1183,1562,1588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Villavicencio</collectorName>
(2004) were the first to cite the type (in the work as “ 
<typeStatus box="[459,564,1598,1625]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">holotype</typeStatus>
”) the material deposited in the 
<collectionCode box="[908,927,1599,1625]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" type="Herbarium">B</collectionCode>
herbarium, however, this cannot be considered a lectotypification because it was published after 2001 and the “designated here” or a similar phrase was not used (
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[143,363,1670,1696]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" refId="ref7456" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="proceedings" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[240,297,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
, Art. 7.11). Although the authors of the species are German and the plant was cultivated in Horto Berolinensis, we cannot say with certainty that the material deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[955,974,1707,1733]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" type="Herbarium">B</collectionCode>
is the 
<typeStatus box="[1050,1148,1706,1732]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">holotype</typeStatus>
because it is not described in the protologue. Here, it is valuable to remember again the Art. 9 
<collectionCode box="[906,932,1742,1768]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
.1. We designate 
<specimenCode box="[1120,1265,1742,1769]" collectionCode="B" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" type="Herbarium">B100516451</specimenCode>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[1349,1452,1742,1768]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">lectotype</typeStatus>
because this specimen contains branch and preserved leaves
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1526,1841]" box="[189,1284,1814,1841]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,438,1814,1840]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Taxonomical note:—</emphasis>
